Portfolio App
_____________

The Portfolio app makes it easy to set up a portfolio website.
It has a backend system for managing all of your projects.

Requirments word
___________

* PHP 5.4 or greater
* MySQL 
* Apache

Setup
_____

1) Run SQL document sql/Portfolio.sql to setup database. Make sure database is
   called `Portfolio` or change the name of the database in the Portfolio.sql.
2) Change the database connection 'user' and 'password' in config/db.php
   to conncet to your datase.
3) place the contents of portfolioAPP into the root directory of your web server. Make sure the folder
   in public_html is the right name for accessing your web content.
4) If you change the name of 'public_html', make sure to change the image             
   management 'public_html' to its new name, for where to put images. 
5) open up the website to www.domainName.com/admin.
6) in the login form type
	username: 'username'
	password: 'password'
   to enter into the admin area for the first time.
7) hit 'Personal Info' and change the password and username for next time.


